         <abstract>
            <p>In this note, we discuss the reconstruction of periodic Jacobi matrices from spectral data. The method combines ideas and techniques from the algorithms given by Boley and Golub [1], [2], and Ferguson [3], resulting in a numerically stable algorithm applicable to a larger class of problems. The number of initial data items needed for this method equals the number of items in the resulting matrix, namely $2n$.</p>
          </abstract>
